  "prompt": "How do pilots avoid turbulence?",
  "response": "Pilots use several methods to avoid or minimize turbulence:\n\n1. Weather forecasting\n- Check detailed weather reports before and during flight\n- Use onboard weather radar to detect potential turbulent areas\n\n2. Altitude adjustment\n- Fly above or below turbulent air layers\n- Change altitude to find smoother air currents\n\n3. Route planning\n- Choose flight paths that avoid known turbulent regions\n- Adjust route to steer clear of storm systems or jet streams\n\n4. Air traffic control communication\n- Receive real-time information about turbulence from other aircraft\n- Coordinate with controllers to find smoother routes\n\n5. Experience and technology\n- Experienced pilots can anticipate and predict turbulence\n- Modern aircraft have advanced systems to detect and navigate around rough air\n\n6. Time of day considerations\n- Avoid flying during times prone to turbulence, like mid-afternoon when thermal currents are strong\n\n7. Terrain awareness\n- Avoid areas near mountain ranges or regions with significant terrain variations\n\nWhile pilots can't completely eliminate turbulence, these strategies help minimize passenger discomfort and ensure flight safety.",
